Atlantic Avenue, at 109th Street, viewing across the Long Island Railroad tracks and showing a pedestrian walk across the tracks.

P. L. Sperr
May 7, 1934

(1) Atlantic Avenue, east from 109th Street, showing the Long Island Railroad tracks fenced off by a wooden fence and dividing the avenue into two separate lanes. At 110th street is the Clarenceville railroad station.

P. L. Sperr

View 1: May 7, 1934

(2) The railroad station at 110th Street, seen from the north lane of the avenue. On the right is the building of the Morris Park Council of the Knights of Columbus.

P. L. Sperr

View 2: May 7, 1934
